==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nonmodern
<hw>nonmodern</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>not modern; of or
characteristic of an earlier time. Opposite of <ant>modern</ant>.</def>
[Narrower terms: <stype>antebellum</stype>; <stype>fogyish, mossgrown,
mossy, stick-in-the-mud(prenominal), stodgy old-fashioned</stype>;
<stype>medieval, mediaeval, gothic</stype>; <stype>old-time,
quaint</stype>; <stype>unmodernized</stype>; <stype>victorian</stype>;
<stype>old-fashioned, outmoded</stype>; <stype>old-world</stype>]
<see>Also See: <er>old</er>, <er>past</er>.</see>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

